[Appius Claudius, a Decemvir, attempted to enslave Virginia, whose father saved her by slaying her. Uproar followed. The plebs seceded to the Aventine, and were joined by the army. The Decemviri for some time refused to abdicate, but finally the ancient constitution was restored, and new laws passed]
